Package org.neuroph.samples

Provides some basic examples of how to use Neuroph.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
FileIOSample This sample shows how to read from and write to external data sources using Neuroph file IO adapters.
HopfieldSample This sample shows how to create and train Hopfield neural network
IrisClassificationSample This sample shows how to train MultiLayerPerceptron neural network for iris classification problem using Neuroph For more details about training process, error, iterations use NeurophStudio which provides rich environment for training and inspecting neural networks
JDBCSample This sample shows hot to read network input and write network output to database using Neuroph JDBC adapaters.
NormalizationSample This sample shows how to do data normalization in Neuroph.
PerceptronSample This sample shows how to create, train, save and load simple Perceptron neural network
RandomizationSample This sample shows how to use various weight randomization techniques in Neuroph.
XorMultiLayerPerceptronSample This sample shows how to create, train, save and load simple Multi Layer Perceptron for the XOR problem.
XorResilientPropagationSample This sample trains Multi Layer Perceptron network using Resilient Propagation learning rule for the XOR problem.
 

Package org.neuroph.samples Description
